.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-GOVERNANCE-GATE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-governance\-gate \- Evaluate governance policy against dashboard inspect JSON artifacts.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard governance-gate [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Evaluate governance policy against dashboard inspect JSON artifacts.
.PP
Use this when you already have governance\-json and query\-report artifacts and want a policy pass or fail result before promotion.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-policy\-source
choose file or builtin.
.TP
.B \-\-policy
policy file path when using file\-based policy input.
.TP
.B \-\-builtin\-policy
named built\-in policy when using builtin policy input.
.TP
.B \-\-governance
path to dashboard inspect governance JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-queries
path to dashboard inspect query\-report JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
render text or JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-json\-output
optionally write the normalized result JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
open the interactive terminal browser over findings.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Evaluate governance policy against dashboard inspect JSON artifacts.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard governance-gate --policy-source file --policy ./policy.yaml --governance ./governance.json --queries ./queries.json
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
